{"lemma": "بَحْرٌ", "slug": "بَحْرٌ", "root": "ب.ح.ر", "root_slug": "ب-ح-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ب-ح-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "بَحْر", "root": "بحر", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 41}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 5, "pos_tags": ["noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 11}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n1837"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "sea", "fa": "دریا", "ur": "سمندر", "tr": "deniz", "id": "laut", "bn": "সমুদ্র", "es": "mar", "fr": "mer", "de": "Meer", "ru": "море", "zh": "海"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of بَحَرَ (baḥara) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "sea", "examples": [{"text": "فِي الصَّيْفِ، نُحِبُّ قِضَاءَ وَقْتٍ مُمْتَعٍ عَلَى شَوَاطِئِ الْبَحْرِ.", "english": "In the summer, we love spending enjoyable time on the seashore."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "large river"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a noble or great man (possessed of a sea of knowledge, experience and wisdom)"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "poetic meter"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to travel by sea, to make a voyage"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be startled, to be bewildered with fright"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to slit, to cut lengthwise"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to split"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to enlarge, to make wide"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of بَحِرَ (baḥira) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From Proto-West Semitic *baḥr- (“sea”).\n\nDenominal verb from بَحْر (baḥr, “sea”)."}, "ipa": ["/baħr/", "/baħ.ħa.ra/", "/ba.ħi.ra/", "/ba.ħa.ra/", "/ba.ħar/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n1837", "headword_ar": "بَحْرٌ", "root": "bHr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A sea:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a great river:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a spacious place comprising a large quantity of water;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(B;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a large quantity of water,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whether salt or sweet;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bar~N", "text_ar": "بَرٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, A;) so called because of its depth (S, TA) and large extent; (S, Msb, TA;) from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbaHaArapu", "text_ar": "البَحَارَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (A;) or because its bed is trenched in the earth; see 1: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a large quantity of salt water,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "only; (K;) and so called because of its saltness: (El-Umawee, TA: [but accord. to the A, this word as an epithet meaning “ salt ” is tropical:]) or rather this is its general meaning: (TA:) for it signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any great river;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any river of which the water does not cease to flow;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, T, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as the Euphrates,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for instance; (S;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as the Tigris, and the Nile, and other similar great rivers of sweet water; of which the great salt"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baHor", "text_ar": "بَحْر"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is the place of confluence;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so called because trenched in the earth: (T, TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aboHurN", "text_ar": "اَبْحُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biHaArN", "text_ar": "بِحَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buHuwrN", "text_ar": "بُحُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, Msb, K.) The dim. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ubayoHirN", "text_ar": "اُبَيْحِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) which is anomalous; and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buHayorN", "text_ar": "بُحَيْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is the regular form: accord. to the K, the latter is not used; but this is untrue; for it is sometimes used, though rare. (MF.) ―         -b2-  Hence its application in the saying of the Arabs,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA haAdiYa", "text_ar": "يَا هَادِىَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "All~ayoli jurota A_in~amaA huwa AlbaHoru A^awi Alfajoru", "text_ar": "اللَّيْلِ جُرْتَ اـِنَّمَا هُوَ البَحْرُ اَوِ الفَجْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which Th explains by saying that the meaning is, (tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O guide of the night, thou hast deviated from the right way:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is only destruction or"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thou wilt see"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the daybreak:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the night is here likened to the sea [and with the night is associated the idea of destruction]: but accord. to one recital, it is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albajoru", "text_ar": "البَجْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", instead of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbaHoru", "text_ar": "البَحْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA. [See art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bjr", "text_ar": "بجر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Salt;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as an epithet, applied to water. (S, A.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A fleet,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "swift, and excellent, horse;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that runs much;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that takes a wide range in his running;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Msb, B;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that runs like the sea,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a great river;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like the sea,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a great river, when it rolls wave over wave."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Niftaweyh;, TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A generous man;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one who takes a wide range in his beneficence, bounty,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kindness; who abounds therein."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqiytu bizayodK baHorFA", "text_ar": "لَقِيتُ بِزَيْدٍ بَحْرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I found, in the place of Zeyd, a man of abundant generosity"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beneficence"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "b", "text_ar": "ب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "here denoting substitution. (The Lubáb cited in the TA voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqiytu minohu baHorFA", "text_ar": "لَقِيتُ مِنْهُ بَحْرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I found him to be a man of exceeding generosity"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; a phrase expressing an intensive degree of generosity: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raA^ayotu minohu", "text_ar": "رَاَيْتُ مِنْهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baHorFA", "text_ar": "بَحْرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[signifies the same]. (Mughnee in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A man of extensive knowledge"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "science; one who takes a wide range in his knowledge"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "science."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(B.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Any person,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thing, that takes a wide range in a thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(B.) ―         -b8-  (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Land of seed-produce and fruitfulness;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a tract,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "region, in which are green herbs"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "leguminous plants, and waters;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "part of a country near to water;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riyfN", "text_ar": "رِيفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Aboo-' Alee, K:) and the dim. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buHayorN", "text_ar": "بُحَيْرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used in the same sense; or, by poetic licence, for ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buHayorapN", "text_ar": "بُحَيْرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) So in the Kur [xxx. 40],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zahara AlfasaAdu fiY Albar~i wa AlbaHori", "text_ar": "ظَهَرَ الفَسَادُ فِى البَرِّ وَ البَحْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Corruption hath appeared in the desert,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "deserts,"}, {"kind"